{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775811484483,"sessionID":"ses_2896686e8ffeDN30MuvZxLFY1v","part":{"id":"prt_d769bbd91001HQOOvWbTIx8k2Z","messageID":"msg_d769b97f0001MJe6zLejtwbcS6","sessionID":"ses_2896686e8ffeDN30MuvZxLFY1v","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7d1a831f51114003827be839","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Overview\n\nExtract shared types (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`) and constants from `codeinterpreter_types.go` into dedicated files, establishing a clear ownership model for the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package.\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe current codebase has several organizational issues:\n\n1. **`TargetPort`** is defined in `codeinterpreter_types.go` but consumed by both `AgentRuntimeSpec.Ports` and `CodeInterpreterSpec.Ports`. This creates an implicit cross-CRD dependency and makes it unclear where new shared types should go.\n\n2. **`ProtocolType`** and its constants (`ProtocolTypeHTTP`, `ProtocolTypeHTTPS`) live in `codeinterpreter_types.go` despite being semantically generic — any future CRD that exposes network ports would need to reference them.\n\n3. **No dedicated file for shared types.** As the API surface grows (e.g., future CRDs like `SessionManager`, `Gateway`), there is no canonical location for types shared across CRDs.\n\n4. **Kind constants and `SchemeGroupVersion`** are split between `register.go` and `groupversion_info.go`. While functional, the separation is inconsistent with the kubebuilder convention of a single `groupversion_info.go`.\n\n## Goals\n\n- Provide a canonical home for types and constants shared across CRDs within the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n- Maintain 100% backward compatibility — no import path changes, no API-breaking renames.\n- Keep CRD-specific types (`AuthModeType`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, `SandboxTemplate`) in their respective type files.\n- Ensure `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` continues to regenerate correctly.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Multi-version API support (v1beta1, v2, etc.)\n- CRD validation webhook scaffolding\n- Conversion webhook setup\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── doc.go                        # unchanged\n├── groupversion_info.go          # merge: absorb SchemeGroupVersion + Resource() from register.go\n├── types.go                      # NEW: shared types (TargetPort, ProtocolType)\n├── constants.go                  # NEW: shared constants (ProtocolTypeHTTP, ProtocolTypeHTTPS)\n├── agent_type.go                 # remove TargetPort/ProtocolType references → import from types.go (same package, no import change)\n├── codeinterpreter_types.go      # remove TargetPort/ProtocolType/AuthModeType → keep only AuthModeType + CRD types\n├── register.go                   # REMOVE: contents merged into groupversion_info.go\n├── zz_generated.deepcopy.go      # regenerated\n└── *_test.go                     # updated to match new file layout\n```\n\n### New File: `types.go`\n\nContains types shared across multiple CRDs within the same API version.\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\n// ProtocolType defines the network protocol for port exposure.\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n\tProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n\tProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n)\n\n// TargetPort describes a network port exposed by a sandbox runtime.\ntype TargetPort struct {\n\tPathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n\tName       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n\tPort       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n\tProtocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Rationale:** `ProtocolType` and its constants are co-located because the constants have no meaning without the type. `TargetPort` is placed in the same file because it is the primary consumer of `ProtocolType` and is itself shared.\n\n### New File: `constants.go`\n\nReserved for future shared constants that are not tied to a specific type (e.g., well-known annotation keys, label selectors, default values). Initially empty or minimal:\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\n// Well-known annotation keys used across AgentCube CRDs.\nconst (\n\tAnnotationKeyRuntime = \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\n\tAnnotationKeyVersion = \"agentcube.io/version\"\n)\n```\n\n**Rationale:** These annotation strings are currently duplicated inline in test files. Centralizing them prevents drift and enables `kubectl get` label selectors to reference a single source of truth.\n\n### Modified: `groupversion_info.go`\n\nAbsorbs the contents of `register.go` to follow the kubebuilder convention of a single group-version info file:\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/scheme\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n\n\t// SchemeGroupVersion is an alias to GroupVersion for backward compatibility\n\t// with client-go generated code that references this name.\n\tSchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n\n\tSchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n\n\tAddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n)\n\n// Resource returns the GroupVersionResource for the given resource name.\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n\treturn GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n}\n\n// Kind constants for both CRDs.\nvar (\n\tCodeInterpreterKind             = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n\tCodeInterpreterGroupKind        = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n\tCodeInterpreterListKind         = \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n\tCodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n\n\tAgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n\tAgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n\tAgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n)\n```\n\n### Modified: `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n\nRemove `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort`. Keep `AuthModeType` (CRD-specific) and the CodeInterpreter CRD types:\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\n// AuthModeType defines the authentication mode for CodeInterpreter.\ntype AuthModeType string\n\nconst (\n\tAuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n\tAuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n)\n\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype CodeInterpreter struct { ... }\n\n// ... (CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, CodeInterpreterList unchanged)\n```\n\n### Modified: `agent_type.go`\n\nNo structural changes — `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` remain accessible because they are in the same package. The file continues to compile without modification.\n\n### Deleted: `register.go`\n\nAll contents merged into `groupversion_info.go`. The `Resource()` helper and Kind constants are now co-located with `GroupVersion` and `SchemeBuilder`.\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\n| Concern | Resolution |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Import paths | No change — all types remain in `package v1alpha1` |\n| Type names | No renames — `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolTypeHTTP`, etc. keep their identifiers |\n| JSON serialization | Unchanged — struct tags are preserved |\n| `SchemeGroupVersion` alias | Preserved for client-go generated code |\n| `Resource()` helper | Preserved with identical signature |\n| Kind constants | Preserved with identical names and values |\n| DeepCopy methods | Regenerated by `make gen-client`; `TargetPort.DeepCopyInto` is a no-op copy (all fields are value types) |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `types_test.go` | `ProtocolType` constant values, `TargetPort` zero-value defaults, `TargetPort` DeepCopy isolation |\n| `constants_test.go` | Well-known annotation key values |\n| `groupversion_info_test.go` (updated) | All Kind constants, `SchemeGroupVersion` alias, `Resource()` helper, scheme registration for both CRDs |\n| `agent_type_test.go` (unchanged) | Existing tests continue to pass — `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` are still accessible from the same package |\n| `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` (unchanged) | Existing tests continue to pass — `AuthModeType` remains in the same file |\n\n### Test Cases for `types_test.go`\n\n```\nTestProtocolTypeConstants\n  - ProtocolTypeHTTP == \"HTTP\"\n  - ProtocolTypeHTTPS == \"HTTPS\"\n  - ProtocolTypeHTTP != ProtocolTypeHTTPS\n\nTestTargetPortDefaults\n  - Zero-value TargetPort: Port==0, empty Name/PathPrefix, empty Protocol\n\nTestTargetPortWithAllFields\n  - All fields set, verify JSON tags\n\nTestTargetPortDeepCopy\n  - DeepCopy produces independent copy\n  - Modifying copy does not affect original\n```\n\n### Test Cases for `constants_test.go`\n\n```\nTestWellKnownAnnotationKeys\n  - AnnotationKeyRuntime == \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\n  - AnnotationKeyVersion == \"agentcube.io/version\"\n```\n\n### Regression Tests\n\nRun the full existing test suite to verify no breakage:\n\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v\n```\n\nAll existing tests must pass without modification (same-package visibility ensures `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` remain accessible).\n\n## Code Generation\n\nAfter file restructuring, regenerate:\n\n```bash\nmake gen-client\n```\n\nThis runs `hack/update-codegen.sh` which invokes `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch`. Expected output:\n\n- `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` — regenerated with `TargetPort` DeepCopy methods (no functional change, as `TargetPort` contains only value types)\n- `client-go/` — no changes (generated code references types by package, not by file)\n\n## Migration Steps\n\n1. Create `types.go` with `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort`\n2. Create `constants.go` with well-known annotation keys\n3. Merge `register.go` contents into `groupversion_info.go`\n4. Delete `register.go`\n5. Remove `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort` from `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n6. Create `types_test.go` and `constants_test.go`\n7. Update `register_test.go` → rename to `groupversion_info_test.go` (or merge)\n8. Run `make gen-client` to regenerate DeepCopy\n9. Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v` to verify\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| `make gen-client` fails due to file reorganization | The code generator scans the package, not individual files. As long as `doc.go` markers and type definitions are intact, regeneration succeeds. |\n| External consumers import specific files | Go imports are at the package level, not file level. No external breakage possible. |\n| Merge conflicts during active development | This is a small, self-contained refactoring (S size). Should be merged during a low-activity window. |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterp